<img width="1080" height="1080" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image lazyload" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut.jpg 1080w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-58x58.jpg 58w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-116x116.jpg 116w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-600x600.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px" /> Hair is significant in the life of a man, being one of the few facial features that influence people’s first impression of him. It also boosts the confidence of a man, pushing him to push beyond the ordinary boundaries of life. Lastly, hair is a form of expression, giving men a platform to share a glimpse of their personalities with the rest of the world. However, like every good and important thing in the world, hair can make or destroy the appearance. An unpopular saying goes, “with hair on a head comes great responsibility.” We live in a society where appearance is everything, and that everything includes your hair. Gone are the days when bad or unkempt hairstyles were looked over. Now having the perfect hairstyle is everything, from attracting that beautiful girl at school to impressing your boss at work. In this article, we listed five amazing hairstyles suitable for you to try out next time you go to a barbershop. ·      Smooth and wavy fade <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1671624 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave-671x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1140" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave-671x598.jpg 671w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave-269x240.jpg 269w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave-539x480.jpg 539w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave-600x534.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/afro-taper-fade-with-wave.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Want something that screams cool and fresh? Look, no further, bruh, this is the perfect hairstyle for you. Everything about this hairstyle feels right, from the incredible texture to the sleek 360 waves, and the side fade. With this hairstyle on your head, you might start a controversial opinion poll, asking who wore it better; you or drake. · Faux Hawk with side fade <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1671622 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-58x58.jpg 58w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-116x116.jpg 116w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Faux-Hawk.jpg 1045w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> If you are the type of man that loves to impress ladies who are into edgy guys, kindly consider this. A Faux hawk is a show stopper on its own, but when paired with a side fade and a nice facial hair cut, it becomes a masterpiece. Popularly referred to as the fohawk, this hairstyle transforms you from a hopeless romantic to the kind of guy other guys want to be like, and every lady wants to be seen with. ·      Skin fade with curly top <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1671619 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-58x58.jpg 58w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-116x116.jpg 116w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Haircut.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> The classic hairstyle for the classy man. It adds an element of modernity and artistry to your general appearance. A notable feature of this hairstyle is the way it plays with shape and style, seeming innovative and also fashion-forward. It also makes its wearer look cool and handsome, buttressing the point, “you can never go wrong with curly hair.” ·      Curved flat tops Nostalgia for the 1950s’ looks much better with this hairstyle. While several hairstyles should stay in the past where they belong, this stands out. It’s a hairstyle where the hair gets cut short to be able to stand right. Fashion is all about risk-taking and being a trendsetter; this hairstyle is one of the ways to do so. · Dreadlocks Joeboy | Image: Idris Dawodu Gone are the days when only people born with natural dreadlocks were allowed to flaunt their incredible hair, now, thanks to hair products and professional barbers, a natural low-cut can also have dreads. Contrary to unpopular opinions that view people with dreads in a negative light, having dreadlocks is fun and makes you appear unique. It also celebrates African culture, upholding our values. Note; Dreadlocks look so much better when properly maintained. Beware: the twisted locks on your head might earn you the historical record of being the first guy who gets catcalled by a group of women. Bonus: Dyeing <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1671621 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair-449x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1706" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair-449x598.jpg 449w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair-180x240.jpg 180w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair-360x480.jpg 360w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair-450x600.jpg 450w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Dyed-Hair.jpg 736w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Hair colour is a fast-growing trend in our society. Different colours like blonde, orange, pink and white are explored when it comes to changing hair colour. Tap into this trend and combine it with one of the hairstyles listed above. For example, you could opt for a skin fade with a grey curly top. Looks like a hair wrap. Remember, your hair is very important as not just a man but a person; maybe that’s probably why Little Mix sang an entire song about it. Hope you enjoyed reading this article? Kindly share the link with your friends.